tourBios.intlVics: (7) 2003 FNB Botswana Open [SAf]. 2006 Eskom Power Cup [SAf]. 2008 Seekers Travel Pro-Am [SAf]. 2009 Vodacom Business [SAf]. 2012 Wild Waves Golf Challenge [SAf], Vodacom Origins-Sishen [SAf], Nedbank Affinity Cup [SAf].
tourBios.carHigh:
Since turning pro in 2002, has competed in 121 South African Tour events and 16 European Tour events (through 2013).

2013: Played 17 tournaments on the South Africa Tour, with his best finish a third-place showing at the Dimension Data Pro-Am in February...Fired a 62 the week before in the Joburg Open to finish T6...Added another 62 in the Wild Wales Golf Challenge in September...Had seven top-10s and nine top-25s...Finished the year 63rd, with $251,985 in earnings...Made five European Tour starts, making two cuts. Best finish was a T27 in the Africa Open.

2012: In South Africa, won three times, at the Wild Waves Golf Challenge, the Vodacom Origins-Sishen and the Nedbank Affinity Cup. Added a runner-up performance and a third-place showing, tallying a total of eight top-10s and 12 top-25s. Made 17 of 19 cuts to finish third on the order of merit, with $856,558 in earnings.

2006: Missed the cut at the Henrico County Open on the Web.com Tour.

2005: In his Web.com Tour debut, missed the cut at the Henrico County Open.
tourBios.personal: Earliest golf memory was making a double eagle...If not a professional golfer, he would be a Moto GP rider or a race car driver...Favorite course he's played is Leopard Creek in Malelane, South Africa...Would like to play Augusta National...Favorite TV show is "Counting Cars" and favorite movie is "The Godfather"...Favorite entertainers are Elvis Presley, Tupac Shakur and Kenny G...Favorite food is Thai and favorite athlete is Valentino Rossi, an Italian motorcycle racer who "I would like to trade places with for one day, riding on the edge."...Favorite city/vacation spot is Durban, South Africa...Dream foursome would feature his dad, Mike Tyson and Al Pacino...Motto is "Be happy, smile and enjoy the journey."...Is involved with his family church's charity efforts...First-tee introduction song would be "Eye of the Tiger."
